The paper discusses the performance of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and Fully-Connected Networks (FCNs) on spatially structured data, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also explores the dynamics of the loss landscape, which is a topic in optimization (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of prior knowledge in the architecture of neural networks, which is a topic in control systems (cs.SY).
